            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Yes, please stick to the issue as-is. Personal comments are completely unacceptable here.\n\nAt the face of it, this request is reasonable at the treesitter level, but I don't think (N)Vim itself supports multiple languages in a single buffer (and all the capture does is hook into the existing spell engine by showing or suppressing spelling error diagnostics). So such a capture would be useless and hence not worth adding.",
